Lets take a look at feudal society as an example for you narrow minded people who could not grasp the overall concept in Thumps post. The people at the top will continually gain in wealth and power and the people at the bottom will consistently struggle and stay at their low status. The system allows for little movement between classes and The landowners can ensure they stay atop the totem pole, while the people under them always remain there. The economic example is much more accurate to the world of EQ and the effects people can have on one another.<br>
