<br>
My guild was once trained with Lodizal while buffing up for it by a guy who post alot about rules on these boards atm. Most of us were lvl 50 and after Lodizal had eaten us, the other guild, now disbanded, killed him. We petitioned cause its not right to train other people. I dont like whining and PnP but training is lame. A lvl 40 monk can make sure a full IV raid fails to Trakanon. I have a screenshot where a guild on Fennin Ro gets trained with 6 other dragons while trying to kill Myga.<br>
<br>
In neither case did a GM observe the action and nothing happened. Well, they get angry but move on. But this just gets a circle going. Manners gets worse and enviroment gets spoiled. Like Topics I played on TZ and even though a guild had the power to kill Trakanon it was prevented several times by a single monk from a cross teamer guild. Petitions are rare on a PvP server and some may call it whining but when 1 individual ruins the game for a whole guild......thats too lame just too ignore and move on. (If you played PvP you will know that you cant prevent a guy hitting you with 20+ mobs even thought you can attack him.)<br>
<br>
This is stuff that can happen when moral is going bad on a server. I dont say thats right or wrong and I'm not to judge. What you do within the rules of the game is up to you and not me. But what I do within the rules is also my own choise. So lets get down to the point.<br>
<br>
I played a little game with some persons of a guild on this server (Fill in the names yourselfs, it shouldnt be very hard). I told someone that if they jumped (by my views not verants rules) my guild taking down something I would bend the rules to the extreme to suit my own needs towards them. An example could be. I order my guild to follow the guild in question on their Vulak raid. Its always nice to observe and since Jaydrox statet at Ragefire that everyone can be whereever they like at all times it should be no problem. They jump Vulak and almost succeeds after a huge effort, but alas, they lose in the end with Vulak at low life. Vulak loses aggro. Hey, its non aggro. I means, wow, CHARGE. We kill the mob. Thanks for the preparations, would you like to see our loot?<br>
<br>
So later on I was contacted by another member of that guild trying to convince me that it was wrong of me to take such actions. One of the arguments was that guild B waiting for guild A to fail couldnt kill the mob alone, but Verants rules dosnt mention this anywhere, so again its subjective views and who cares about those? Nobody, we use the rules. I asked why I was wrong and he was right? It was merely the same as his guild had been doing just on a grander scale. After a few minutes exchanging arguments, in a friendly manner all the way, he wasnt able to prove me wrong. Its easy to argue when you can use peoples own arguments.<br>
<br>
This is not a rant but a try to open some eyes. This game is played for fun and you cant guarantee fun for all but its only fun as long as it isnt YOU who get stomped. Its easy for the big guys to stomp the small but its not impossible for the small to stop the big guys.<br>
<br>
This server is far from ruined. Its a good server and just as Wumple points out, I have lots of fun playing. I'm even proud of the uberguild from Vaz when I speak with my friends from other servers. I have many friends and few enemies though I see the risk of this post getting me a few. (Dont visit the boards if you dont want enemies, people comin here have way too much time on their hands, including myself) As many people seems to have forgot I was one of the people that 'forced' this server to become FFA. I'm a strong supporter of FFA but I'm also a strong supporter of mutual respect.<br>
<br>
If guild A made a load of work to get to mob X, I belive its good manners to let them have fun trying it. If guild B wants to kill it while guild A is doing CR, fine with me but expect everyone else to play by those rules and try not to point out why you can and they can't.<br>
<br>
Draw whatever conclusions you want from this post. I was bored at work and had to post something.<br>
