<br>
Just like you need to be a certain level before you can kill various mobs, you also need to have a certain level of dedication to do some of the bigger activities in the game such as plane raids.<br>
<br>
The calendar isn't part of the game.  It's a communication tool, not the law.  It may suit your play style, but it's not ideal for others.  Personally, I don't like calendars.  However, this isn't a debate about the calendar.<br>
<br>
You're depending on a tool which is unreliable.  It's not going to guarantee your guild a trip to a plane.  Believing that it will, depending on it to do that for you will lead to the disappointment that you and your guildmates felt.<br>
<br>
There was a high end game in TeamFortress.  There were top clans and leagues.  In order to play at that high level, you needed to be dedicated.  You needed to play a ton to get your skills up to make the clan, and once in, you would usually need to attend two practices and two to three matches a week.  It was relatively demanding, and not everyone could cut it.  Most people wanted to be in a top 10 clan, but most would never be.  That was disappointing to a lot of people, but that's part of the nature of the game, that's life.  You get back what you put in.<br>
<br>
The high end game in EverQuest requires dedication too.  You need to play a lot.  You need to be in a guild who plays a lot, and if you want to kill the same mob as another guild, you will either need to make arrangements with them or race them to it.  Most players want to see Veeshans Peak and Sleepers Tomb, most players will not.<br>
<br>
In the case of Fear, it is a plane that you will usually get away with scheduling.  The respawn is only 12 hours for most mobs, so most guilds don't mind waiting a day or two.  The only time a guild like IV needs to be there is to kill Cazic or to kill a mob needed for an epic, and Cazic will usually only be up one or two days a week.<br>
<br>
You seem like a nice guy, and I empathize with you and everyone else,  but life changes in the high end game.  Sometimes things change in ways we don't like or in a way that doesn't suit us.  That's life. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ugenobi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>genobi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Junior Member</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/7/01 11:32:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server's attitue, not a rant but a plea!</span><hr size=1> Ceros,<br>
