<br>
I simply believe that guilds have the right to play like this, and believed that even when I was in a guild that was being stepped on.<br>
<br>
A distinction needs to be made as well.  Large guilds or 'uber' guilds generally aren't loot driven, we're accomplishment driven.  We're ambitious.  We have goals, and need those items to accomplish our goals effectively.  It's not about personal greed.  I, like other members, gave my best items back to the guild when I left EQ -- even knowing that I'd probably be back some day anyway, heh.<br>
