<br>
Soliid<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
As many have said due to the climate of the server, people have no choice to race.  I'm not trying to argue the merits of scheduling/not scheduling--but to say that The Endless or any other guild you listed race for any other reason than being forced to race, in my opinion is less than correct.  <br>
<br>
You are not evil for racing to a mob.  Racing is not necessarily wrong either.  But Baldrik put it the best...  it is about respect and having fun.  <br>
<br>
I understand the desire for competition.  I know what it feels like to get pumped up before a match.  I just wonder if the thrill is in accomplishing something--or ruining someone else's fun.  Or is the thrill in a piece of gaining an item.  Yes, I understand that X item is important to do bigger things.  But is it worth taking away positive experiences from others.    <br>
<br>
BTW, I honestly do believe that most people like to earn the goodies they get.  Just tossing someone &quot;scraps&quot; isn't really rewarding--except for the individuals that are truely loot-centric.  <br>
<br>
As many have expressed...  I fear that things can only get worse from here.  With the level cap of 60--eventually things will level out.  When everyone is on a fairly level field, things will get even more competitive.  Things will get ugly.  You know the training, KS'ing, PnP'ing that happens on other servers--prepare to see it in a zone near you....  UNLESS, people take pro-active steps to fix things.  <br>
<br>
You don't have to do anything really...  As long as you play by the letter of the law, you can play the game as you like.  But I believe, like everything--there is a spirit of the law which is lacking and that will eventually turn Vaz into major chaos.  <br>
<br>
G'adventuring to you all.  <br>
<br>
--Bakxs   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utropicsdelight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TropicsDelight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Junior Member</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/7/01 8:19:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I would like to beg to differ...</span><hr size=1> I dont mind racing to a mob either. I do think guild_01 winning the race to the mob and then having guild_02 push them out of the way and taking the spawn from under their nose smells just a little of poor play style.<br>
