<br>
&quot;You may not steal kills.<br>
Kill Stealing is defined as the killing of an NPC for any reason that is already fighting or pursuing another player or group without that group's specific permission.&quot;<br>
<br>
From everquest.com. Dosnt state anything about a mobs life so its up to the server GM to resolve the issue. Maybe you're right and maybe you would try to petition the party involved, but if the GM didnt see it I'm not sure he would do anything.<br>
<br>
But if you really are rulemongers did IV contact a GM when they pulled CT in front of TE/SF? Cause:<br>
<br>
&quot;You must comply with arbitration for contested spawns.<br>
There are cases where two or more groups wish to kill the same thing. In these cases, the groups are required to compromise. If an equitable compromise cannot be reached between the players prior to EverQuest Customer Service Staff involvement, the EQCSR will mandate a binding compromise. Refusing to abide by a compromise mandated by an EQCSR will be considered disruption. It is therefore strongly suggested that the groups make every attempt to reach a compromise that they can live with prior to involving an EQCSR, who may mandate a compromise that does not suit you to the extent that a player-devised compromise would&quot;<br>
<br>
Again the answer is no even though rules stated they should. I agree that following those rules to the letter is boring. But again we return to respect. I'm sure that TE/SF could be persuaded to take one more try and if they failed, IV could have the spawn. That would prolly be what the GM would have told the involved parties but was dialog attampted? I doubt it, from what I heard the puller just took the mob.<br>
<br>
Its the name of the game, competition, and Ceros points our Trakanon would be, and is, a race. Thats cool, we wanted to race TE to Trakanon once but we didnt have the people online before TE was at reets and pulling the lair. At that point its their try in my book.<br>
<br>
Again I'm not trying to whine or cry cause noone stole anything from CC yet and I have no reason to belive it will happen often. (I'm sleeping when most of this stuff happens) What makes me rant at this issue is the double moral.<br>
<br>
Lets say that you are camping Fingerbone hoop in Howling Stones. I pop by with a group and begin to pull mobs in south wing, the same spawns as you want. Would you just say: &quot;Hey, thats competition, cool.&quot; or would I be called lame and gay in ooc for stealing your camp? I think the last because it would suck for everyone if the server became like that. Its again a question about respect just at a lower level this time. Competition is nice but friendly competition is prefered.<br>
